{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-971d8fa9f82759c1", "type": "tool_result", "content": "=== 2603.13686 ===\n# $τ$-Voice: Benchmarking Full-Duplex Voice Agents on Real-World Domains\narXiv: 2603.13686\nAuthors: Soham Ray, Keshav Dhandhania, Victor Barres, Karthik Narasimhan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_agent\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A voice agent benchmark combining verifiable completion of complex grounded tasks, full-duplex interaction, and realistic audio.\n  2. A controllable and realistic voice user simulator with diverse accents, realistic audio environments, and rich turn-taking dynamics.\n  3. Empirical findings revealing a substantial voice-text gap where voice agents retain only 30-45% of text capability under realistic conditions.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/基准, Eval/情感语境交互, Eval/安全性, Agent, Agent/对话型LALM\n=== 2508.07375 ===\n# TurnGuide: Enhancing Meaningful Full Duplex Spoken Interactions via Dynamic Turn-Level Text-Speech Interleaving\narXiv: 2508.07375\nAuthors: Wenqian Cui, Lei Zhu, Xiaohui Li, Zhihan Guo, Haoli Bai, Lu Hou, Irwin King\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: dialogue_system\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose TurnGuide, a novel text-speech interleaved generation approach for end-to-end full-duplex speech language models grounded in natural speech data.\n  2. We introduce a dynamic turn segmentation framework to address the insertion timing and length challenges of integrating text into double-channel dialogues.\n  3. We introduce a text-guided dialogue modeling framework that interleaves text and speech generation at the turn level to preserve natural acoustic flow.\n  4. We demonstrate through extensive experiments that TurnGuide significantly improves the semantic coherence of generated speech and achieves state-of-the-art performance on turn-taking events.\n\nTags: LALM/对话型-交错标记, LALM/对话型-纯语音, Agent/全双工\n=== 2604.04847 ===\n# Full-Duplex-Bench-v3: Benchmarking Tool Use for Full-Duplex Voice Agents Under Real-World Disfluency\narXiv: 2604.04847\nAuthors: Guan-Ting Lin, Chen Chen, Zhehuai Chen, Hung-yi Lee\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Authentic human speech with systematic disfluency annotation enables fine-grained robustness analysis across five categories.\n  2. Self-correction and state rollback scenarios test whether models can recognize mid-utterance intent changes and correctly update downstream API parameters.\n  3. Multi-step function chaining across four task domains requires sequential API calls with fully deterministic outputs for automatic scoring.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/基准, Eval/情感语境交互, Agent, Agent/Action\n=== 2603.24038 (VAP) ===\n# ACAVCaps: Enabling large-scale training for fine-grained and diverse audio understanding\narXiv: 2603.24038\nAuthors: Yadong Niu, Tianzi Wang, Heinrich Dinkel, Xingwei Sun, Jiahao Zhou, Gang Li, Jizhong Liu, Junbo Zhang, Jian Luan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of ACAVCaps, a large-scale, fine-grained, and multi-faceted audio captioning dataset derived from the ACAV100M collection.\n  2. Development of a multi-expert pipeline that analyzes audio from diverse perspectives and synthesizes the outputs into rich descriptions using a Chain-of-Thought enhanced large language model.\n  3. Demonstration that models pre-trained on ACAVCaps generate superior fine-grained audio captions compared to those trained on other leading captioning datasets.\n  4. Validation that models pre-trained on ACAVCaps exhibit stronger generalization capabilities across diverse downstream speech, music, and sound event tasks, proving that semantic complexity and data quality outweigh raw sample volume.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "c806aa2b-0d14-445a-bd13-a3c942dc7125", "uuid": "69cbc861-6ce2-4cae-b55d-089f5f368694", "timestamp": "2026-07-12T17:23:03.595Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "=== 2603.13686 ===\n# $τ$-Voice: Benchmarking Full-Duplex Voice Agents on Real-World Domains\narXiv: 2603.13686\nAuthors: Soham Ray, Keshav Dhandhania, Victor Barres, Karthik Narasimhan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_agent\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A voice agent benchmark combining verifiable completion of complex grounded tasks, full-duplex interaction, and realistic audio.\n  2. A controllable and realistic voice user simulator with diverse accents, realistic audio environments, and rich turn-taking dynamics.\n  3. Empirical findings revealing a substantial voice-text gap where voice agents retain only 30-45% of text capability under realistic conditions.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/基准, Eval/情感语境交互, Eval/安全性, Agent, Agent/对话型LALM\n=== 2508.07375 ===\n# TurnGuide: Enhancing Meaningful Full Duplex Spoken Interactions via Dynamic Turn-Level Text-Speech Interleaving\narXiv: 2508.07375\nAuthors: Wenqian Cui, Lei Zhu, Xiaohui Li, Zhihan Guo, Haoli Bai, Lu Hou, Irwin King\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: dialogue_system\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose TurnGuide, a novel text-speech interleaved generation approach for end-to-end full-duplex speech language models grounded in natural speech data.\n  2. We introduce a dynamic turn segmentation framework to address the insertion timing and length challenges of integrating text into double-channel dialogues.\n  3. We introduce a text-guided dialogue modeling framework that interleaves text and speech generation at the turn level to preserve natural acoustic flow.\n  4. We demonstrate through extensive experiments that TurnGuide significantly improves the semantic coherence of generated speech and achieves state-of-the-art performance on turn-taking events.\n\nTags: LALM/对话型-交错标记, LALM/对话型-纯语音, Agent/全双工\n=== 2604.04847 ===\n# Full-Duplex-Bench-v3: Benchmarking Tool Use for Full-Duplex Voice Agents Under Real-World Disfluency\narXiv: 2604.04847\nAuthors: Guan-Ting Lin, Chen Chen, Zhehuai Chen, Hung-yi Lee\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Authentic human speech with systematic disfluency annotation enables fine-grained robustness analysis across five categories.\n  2. Self-correction and state rollback scenarios test whether models can recognize mid-utterance intent changes and correctly update downstream API parameters.\n  3. Multi-step function chaining across four task domains requires sequential API calls with fully deterministic outputs for automatic scoring.\n\nTags: Eval, Eval/基准, Eval/情感语境交互, Agent, Agent/Action\n=== 2603.24038 (VAP) ===\n# ACAVCaps: Enabling large-scale training for fine-grained and diverse audio understanding\narXiv: 2603.24038\nAuthors: Yadong Niu, Tianzi Wang, Heinrich Dinkel, Xingwei Sun, Jiahao Zhou, Gang Li, Jizhong Liu, Junbo Zhang, Jian Luan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduction of ACAVCaps, a large-scale, fine-grained, and multi-faceted audio captioning dataset derived from the ACAV100M collection.\n  2. Development of a multi-expert pipeline that analyzes audio from diverse perspectives and synthesizes the outputs into rich descriptions using a Chain-of-Thought enhanced large language model.\n  3. Demonstration that models pre-trained on ACAVCaps generate superior fine-grained audio captions compared to those trained on other leading captioning datasets.\n  4. Validation that models pre-trained on ACAVCaps exhibit stronger generalization capabilities across diverse downstream speech, music, and sound event tasks, proving that semantic complexity and data quality outweigh raw sample volume.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
